<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>464</anchor> <rss>rs-0005.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Observation</taxon> <addr>rs-0005</addr>  <route>rs-0005.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>7</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="rileyshahar.xml" type="local">Riley Shahar</link></author> </authors> <title>Categorical duality</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Category theory admits a kind of syntactic duality via the <link href="rs-0004.xml" type="local" title="Opposite category">opposite
category</link>, through which any theorem immediately obtains a
dual via &quot;reversing all the arrows&quot; in the theorem and proof.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>465</anchor> <rss>rs-0004.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>rs-0004</addr>  <route>rs-0004.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>7</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="rileyshahar.xml" type="local">Riley Shahar</link></author> </authors> <title>Opposite category</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Fix a <link href="rs-0001.xml" type="local" title="Category">category</link> <tex>C</tex>. The <em>opposite category</em> <tex>C^{ \text{op} }</tex>    consists of:</p><ul>  <li>the same objects as in <tex>C</tex>;</li>  <li>for each morphism <tex>x \xrightarrow{f}  y</tex> in <tex>C</tex>, a morphism
      <tex>y \xrightarrow{f^{ \text{op} }}  x</tex>.</li></ul><p>Composition is given contrapositively, as in the equality</p><tex display="block">  g^ \text{op} ;f^ \text{op}  = (f;g)^{ \text{op} }.
</tex></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>466</anchor> <rss>rs-001Z.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Observation</taxon> <addr>rs-001Z</addr>  <route>rs-001Z.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>8</month> <day>7</day></date> <authors><author><link href="rileyshahar.xml" type="local">Riley Shahar</link></author> </authors> <title>Order-theoretic duality</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>As a special case of <link href="rs-0005.xml" type="local" title="Categorical duality">categorical duality</link>, every definition in
<link href="rs-001U.xml" type="local" title="Order theory">order theory</link> admits a syntactic dual by reversing the order. We
generally prefer to work in terms of <tex>\leq</tex> rather than <tex>\geq</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>